The course aims to provide the students an opportunity to complement their education with introductory knowledge about the phenomenon called human rights. We shall consider the uprise of human rights in the international legal system and the most relevant developments in the field ― throughout the course tight relationship shall be held with public international law. The emphasis is intended to lay rather on philosophical than technical questions ― i.e. we shall discuss primarily issues relating to the substence, extent and societal function of human rights, leaving questions about the international protection of human rights at the upstage. The study process is intended to have the form of a combination between auditorial and independent work, which means that some materials shall have to be read and a presntation held.Objectives/eesmärkid:  -Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  -
